ty" and finds himself struggling yet again--this time against banality--in his continued quest for freedom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIranians - Canada. 0aIranianszCanada. 0aJahanbegloo, Ramin-Imprisonment. 0aPhilosophers-Canada-Biography. 0aPhilosophers-Iran-Biography. 0aPolitical prisoners-Iran-Biography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Philosophers.2bisacsh  aIran, political, imprisonment, Evin Prison, philosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977341740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889773417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889773417/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles